British construction firm Space and Style recently launched the latest plumbing products in conjunction with local manufacturing firm Space and Style. The event was hosted by British High Commissioner Jane Marriott at her residence in Muthaiga. Present were Space and Style CEO Winnie Ngumi, former KRA boss John Njiraini and director Njoki Muhoho, as well as top executives of Kenyan engineering and manufacturing firms. Mariott reiterated the UK's commitment to working with Kenya to increase trade and investment between the two countries.